======================================================================
PART 1: H-GENERATING POLYNOMIAL P_n(q) = sum_T q^{H(T)}
======================================================================

  n=3: P_3(q) = 6*q^1 + 2*q^3
  P(1) = 8
  P(-1) = -8
  P(0) = 0
  All H odd: P(-1) = -8 = -8

  Q_3(x) where P_3(q) = q * Q_3(q^2):
  Q_3(x) = 6*x^0 + 2*x^1
  Q(1) = 8 = P(1)
  Q(0) = 6 = #{H=1} = n! (transitive tournaments)
  Q(-1) = 4

  n=4: P_4(q) = 24*q^1 + 16*q^3 + 24*q^5
  P(1) = 64
  P(-1) = -64
  P(0) = 0
  All H odd: P(-1) = -64 = -64

  Q_4(x) where P_4(q) = q * Q_4(q^2):
  Q_4(x) = 24*x^0 + 16*x^1 + 24*x^2
  Q(1) = 64 = P(1)
  Q(0) = 24 = #{H=1} = n! (transitive tournaments)
  Q(-1) = 32

  n=5: P_5(q) = 120*q^1 + 120*q^3 + 240*q^5 + 240*q^9 + 120*q^11 + 120*q^13 + 64*q^15
  P(1) = 1024
  P(-1) = -1024
  P(0) = 0
  All H odd: P(-1) = -1024 = -1024

  Q_5(x) where P_5(q) = q * Q_5(q^2):
  Q_5(x) = 120*x^0 + 120*x^1 + 240*x^2 + 240*x^4 + 120*x^5 + 120*x^6 + 64*x^7
  Q(1) = 1024 = P(1)
  Q(0) = 120 = #{H=1} = n! (transitive tournaments)
  Q(-1) = 416

  n=6: P_6(q) = 456*q^1 + 604*q^3 + 1350*q^5 + 1836*q^9 + 886*q^11 + 888*q^13 + 1358*q^15 + 884*q^17 + 878*q^19 + 1746*q^23 + 872*q^25 + 292*q^27 + 1746*q^29 + 876*q^31 + 1588*q^33 + 2168*q^37 + 426*q^41 + 860*q^43 + 286*q^45
  P(1) = 20000
  P(-1) = -20000
  P(0) = 0
  All H odd: P(-1) = -20000 = -20000

======================================================================
PART 2: TWO-VARIABLE G_n(q, t) = sum_T q^{H(T)} * t^{c3(T)}
======================================================================

  n=4: G_4(q, t) = 
    + 24 * q^1 * t^0
    + 16 * q^3 * t^1
    + 24 * q^5 * t^2

  G(1,t) = sum #{c3=k} * t^k:
    + 24 * t^0
    + 16 * t^1
    + 24 * t^2

  Is G separable? G(q,t) = P(q)*R(t)?
    Separable: False

  n=5: G_5(q, t) = 
    + 120 * q^1 * t^0
    + 120 * q^3 * t^1
    + 240 * q^5 * t^2
    + 240 * q^9 * t^3
    + 120 * q^11 * t^4
    + 120 * q^13 * t^4
    + 40 * q^15 * t^4
    + 24 * q^15 * t^5

  G(1,t) = sum #{c3=k} * t^k:
    + 120 * t^0
    + 120 * t^1
    + 240 * t^2
    + 240 * t^3
    + 280 * t^4
    + 24 * t^5

  Is G separable? G(q,t) = P(q)*R(t)?
    Separable: False

