======================================================================
PART 5: I(Omega, lambda) AS FUNCTION OF FUGACITY lambda
  H = I(Omega, 2). What about I(Omega, lambda) for other lambda?
======================================================================

  bits=0: H=1, alpha_1=0
  I(Omega, lambda) = 1 + 0*lambda
    lambda= 0: I = 1
    lambda= 1: I = 1
    lambda= 2: I = 1
    lambda= 3: I = 1
    lambda= 5: I = 1
    lambda=10: I = 1

  bits=42: H=13, alpha_1=6
  I(Omega, lambda) = 1 + 6*lambda
    lambda= 0: I = 1
    lambda= 1: I = 7
    lambda= 2: I = 13
    lambda= 3: I = 19
    lambda= 5: I = 31
    lambda=10: I = 61

  bits=100: H=9, alpha_1=4
  I(Omega, lambda) = 1 + 4*lambda
    lambda= 0: I = 1
    lambda= 1: I = 5
    lambda= 2: I = 9
    lambda= 3: I = 13
    lambda= 5: I = 21
    lambda=10: I = 41

  bits=511: H=1, alpha_1=0
  I(Omega, lambda) = 1 + 0*lambda
    lambda= 0: I = 1
    lambda= 1: I = 1
    lambda= 2: I = 1
    lambda= 3: I = 1
    lambda= 5: I = 1
    lambda=10: I = 1

  bits=1023: H=1, alpha_1=0
  I(Omega, lambda) = 1 + 0*lambda
    lambda= 0: I = 1
    lambda= 1: I = 1
    lambda= 2: I = 1
    lambda= 3: I = 1
    lambda= 5: I = 1
    lambda=10: I = 1

  KEY: At lambda=2, I(Omega,2) = H(T). This is the TOURNAMENT POINT.
  At lambda=3, I(Omega,3) = 1+3*alpha_1 = (3*H-1)/2 at n=5 (since H=1+2*alpha_1)
  So I(Omega,3) = (3*H-1)/2 at n=5!

  Verification: I(Omega,3) = (3*H-1)/2 at n=5:
    All match: True (algebraic identity at n=5)

